14 IN RESPECTFUL MEMORY OF FORMER UNITED
15 STATES REPRESENTATIVE BERYL ANTHONY, JR.
16
17 WHEREAS, former United States Representative Beryl Anthony, Jr.,
18 formerly of El Dorado, passed away on Saturday, January 11, 2025, at the age
19 of eighty-six (86); and
20
21 WHEREAS, Beryl Anthony, Jr. was born in El Dorado, Arkansas, on
22 February 21, 1938, to Beryl Franklin Anthony, Sr. and Oma Lee Roark Anthony,
23 founders of the Anthony Forest Products Company; and
24
25 WHEREAS, Beryl Anthony, Jr. received Bachelor of Science and Bachelor
26 of Arts degrees from the University of Arkansas in 1961, then in 1963 earned
27 his Juris Doctorate from the University of Arkansas School of Law; and
28
29 WHEREAS, Beryl Anthony, Jr. was first elected to public office in 1970,
30 when he won the Union County prosecuting attorney's office, Thirteenth
31 Judicial District, a position he held from 1971 to 1976; and
32
33 WHEREAS, Beryl Anthony, Jr. was first elected to the United States
34 House of Representatives in 1978, serving until 1993, and was appointed to
35 many committees, including the House Ways and Means Committee, where he
36 championed legislation for improved rural healthcare and public
